					In the summer of 1995, the Windy City lost approximately 700 residents in just five humid and sweltering days. As the heat lingered, much of Chicago's urban infrastructure began to break down. Paramedics, hospitals and morgues were quickly overwhelmed. (Photo Credit: AFP/Getty Images)
