					Already battered by the Great Depression, the United States took yet another debilitating hit when temperatures soared in 1936, clearing the 120-degree mark in some regions. Here, New Yorkers seeking relief throng the boardwalk and beach at Coney Island. (Photo Credit: New York Daily News via Getty Images)
